techniqueDifficultyExplanation: This workout involves intermediate to advanced bodyweight exercises such as ring curls, one arm chin-up holds, and commando one arm negatives. These exercises require good coordination, balance, and body awareness, fitting between the Intermediate and Advanced categories. User comments indicate soreness and challenges, suggesting a higher technique demand than simple exercises. The inclusion of equipment like rings and the demands of controlling negatives also elevate the complexity beyond beginner level.
effortDifficultyExplanation: The workout features high-intensity exercises like one arm chin-up holds and negatives over a duration of 11 minutes. Comments mention significant muscle fatigue, indicating a challenging effort requirement. The presence of weight vest and progressive sets implies a potentially high energy expenditure. While not very long, the exercises themselves demand intense effort, categorizing the workout as challenging with a slight lean towards extreme for some less conditioned users.
requiredFitnessLevelExplanation: Due to the challenging nature of the exercises and the intermediate to advanced technique difficulty, this workout is best suited for intermediate users who have some experience in exercise routines and advanced users who can handle the high intensity and technical demands. Beginners are likely to find the workout too technically complex and physically demanding, even with modifications.
